<TITLE> Pakistan's Tanvir ruled out for four months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, Mar 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan all-rounder Sohail Tanvir has been ruled out of cricket for four months due to a knee injury. "Tanvir has had an operation in Australia today for a chronic knee problem and he has been advised to rest for four months," his agent, Salman Ahmed, said. The Pakistan Cricket Board said it had sent Tanvir to Australia for the operation which was performed successfully. Tanvir, 25, who has played two Tests and 31 one-day internationals also opted out of a contract with Australian state side Victoria in December due to the same injury. The left-arm medium-fast bowler last played for Pakistan in November against New Zea
